    "He taught as an instructor of fine arts at the University of Michigan, 1955-56, before moving to Princeton as an associate professor in 1956.": [],
    "In 1960, Rosenblum published his <em>Cubism and Twentieth-Century Art</em>, which solidified his reputation as a new-world modernist.": [
