    "Except for visiting professorships at Columbia University, 1960-61 and 1963, he remained at Princeton until 1966.": [],
    "That year he was appointed professor of fine arts at New York University where he remained the rest of his career.": [],
    "In 1967, Rosenblum took the theme of his dissertation, reworking it as the book <em>Transformations in Late Eighteen-Century Art</em>.": [
        [
            9,
            18,
            [
                "Rosenbaum"
            ]
        ]
    ],
    "This seminal work was based upon the idea of \"turning points\" of works of the early Modern period, an examination of the manner in which the French Revolution adopted neoclassical imagery and techniques.": [],
    "In 1975, Rosenblum participated in a major show of French Revolutionary art at the Metropolitan and Detroit, <em>French Painting, 1774-1830: the Age of Revolution</em>.": [
        [
            9,
            18,
            [
                "Rosenbaum"
